		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />- Are the good times of nesdev gone? Times when I received a lot of e-mails from mailing list within a lot of information... like  e-mails from Mark, bringing a new cart + mapper information to be added into emulators, or the NES sound discussion, mainly from Matt Conte efforts.
<br />
<br />- Heh, it's nostalgic on present days... The last scene came from blargg, releasing full APU information, plus all those test ROMs... very nice. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> It's been a long time since someone has 'found' or asked something interesting about the NES. Of course, it's not the 'basics', the old problems I had during the 'primitive' days are popping up nowadays.
<br />
<br />- Is just me or am I right? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />

		

